1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,120
Rituals, beliefs, and myths in this series are a work of fiction and in no regard refer to religions or faiths of any certain cultures.

2
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:17,080
He did not lie to you, Pete.

3
00:00:17,640 --> 00:00:19,120
He lied to us.

4
00:00:20,160 --> 00:00:21,480
Your sister is awake now.

5
00:00:23,480 --> 00:00:24,200
Shit!

6
00:00:25,080 --> 00:00:25,640
Niran?

7
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:27,880
May your life spirit drift away

8
00:00:28,280 --> 00:00:29,680
and be lost for all eternity,

9
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:33,000
There has to be a way to bring him back.

10
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:34,960
The only person who can save Niran

11
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:36,040
is you.

12
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:40,600
(Once,)

13
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:43,800
(Zhuangzi dreamed he was a butterfly,)

14
00:00:44,840 --> 00:00:47,520
(flitting and fluttering happily about.)

15
00:00:48,840 --> 00:00:54,160
(The butterfly did not have a clue
that he was Zhuangzi.)

16
00:00:55,480 --> 00:00:58,120
(But when Zhuangzi opened his eyes,)

17
00:00:58,920 --> 00:01:01,720
(aware of who he was,)

18
00:01:02,360 --> 00:01:05,720
(Zhuangzi was suddenly
uncertain of what he was.)

19
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:10,200
(Was he Zhuangzi who dreamed
he was a butterfly,)

20
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:16,160
(or a butterfly who dreamed
he spent his whole life as Zhuangzi?)

21
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:07,400
Oh, hey, Niran.

22
00:03:08,480 --> 00:03:12,280
After we defeat Qi Rong,
what are you going to do next?

23
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:16,680
I’d probably continue defeating yao
if someone hires me.

24
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,240
No, that’s not what I meant.

25
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,840
Don’t you have dreams?

26
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:26,079
You know, like, grand plans
you have for your life?

27
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:29,880
Nope.

28
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:31,480
Why?

29
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:32,440
You do?

30
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,000
Actually I think…

31
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:44,600
I might go back to college.

32
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:50,440
I’ve always wanted to do that,
but never had the courage to.

33
00:03:52,320 --> 00:03:53,720
But I realized now

34
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:59,320
that if I don’t do it,
my life wouldn’t mean a thing.

35
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:03,120
That’s nice.

36
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:07,360
I still don’t know what I want to do, though.

37
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:10,360
There’s gotta be something.

38
00:04:10,960 --> 00:04:12,240
I’m sure you’ll know soon.

39
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:17,079
A guy like you wasn’t born
to just coast through life.

40
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:28,360
How about this?

41
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:31,280
Why don’t you help me think

42
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:34,400
what kind of thing
a guy like me should do?

43
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:37,280
Sure thing.

44
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:39,560
I’m not as smart as you.

45
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:42,080
But I’ll do my best to help you.

46
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:47,440
Alright.

47
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:48,720
Cheers.

48
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:49,880
Okay.

49
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:12,520
(You have to look for him
in the Life Spirit Realm.)

50
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:16,600
SUN, WINDOW, RITUAL ALTAR

51
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:21,760
BIG MIRROR (REFLECT YOUR BACK)
MONKEY AND TIGER STUFFIES
AS MEDIUMS

52
00:05:21,760 --> 00:05:23,080
DOOR

53
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:55,080
(The silver lining in this situation is that
Niran’s soul is bound to yours.)

54
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:58,040
(That thread is the thing that will help you.)

55
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:03,080
(The Life Spirit Realm is a land that
does not exist under heaven, )

56
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:04,480
(nor above earth.)

57
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:09,880
(If one must define it, it is comparable
to the reflection in a mirror.)

58
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:12,400
(That world has everything to offer,)

59
00:06:12,680 --> 00:06:14,760
(except the truth.)

60
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:35,640
(To enter that world, there are
three things you need to do.)

61
00:06:36,320 --> 00:06:42,000
First, the Life Spirit Realm is vast
and moves as fast as one’s thoughts.

62
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:45,159
You need to keep in mind
what you’re there for.

63
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:47,120
Do not lose your focus.

64
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:50,800
Second, Niran enters
that world unknowingly.

65
00:06:51,080 --> 00:06:54,400
Once you find him, you need to do
whatever it takes for him to trust you,

66
00:06:54,400 --> 00:06:56,000
and let you guide him back.

67
00:06:56,440 --> 00:07:00,600
Third, a human’s life spirit can
survive without its body for a month,

68
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:02,640
in that world, it is only eight hours.

69
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:04,120
You have to leave within eight hours,

70
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:10,840
otherwise, you will be stuck there
and, eventually, devoured by it.

71
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,800
May the power of heaven and earth

72
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:19,440
bring me into the Life Spirit Realm

73
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,280
to look for Niran.

74
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:10,720
Oh?

75
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:12,800
What are you doing here?

76
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:15,480
What…

77
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:17,280
Well, you know—

78
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:19,000
Come down to breakfast.

79
00:08:19,080 --> 00:08:20,080
Mom asked me to get you.

80
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:20,880
What?

81
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,040
Mom?

82
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:31,480
I’m gaining weight, Dad.

83
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:32,880
Oh, not at all.

84
00:08:33,159 --> 00:08:34,559
This looks good, though.

85
00:08:34,559 --> 00:08:35,400
And it’s good, too.

86
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:37,520
What are you two talking about?

87
00:08:37,520 --> 00:08:39,600
Come on and sit down, honey.

88
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,520
Oh, this is really good.

89
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:46,600
Oh?

90
00:08:46,880 --> 00:08:47,520
Pete.

91
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:49,480
Let’s have breakfast, dear.

92
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,640
It’s 9 o’clock.

93
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:57,360
You think there’s going
to be traffic, honey?

94
00:08:57,480 --> 00:08:59,920
I told you to wake Pete up earlier.

95
00:09:00,360 --> 00:09:01,800
Your brother was just done
with his tournament.

96
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:03,320
I just thought we could
let him rest a little longer.

97
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,800
Come on, you two.

98
00:09:05,200 --> 00:09:07,080
We’ll be fine even if there’s traffic.

99
00:09:07,560 --> 00:09:10,440
It’s best to take it easy
when taking a trip, right, Pete?

100
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:14,400
Yes.

101
00:09:14,680 --> 00:09:15,720
You should have breakfast.

102
00:09:18,040 --> 00:09:19,920
Breakfast is super good today.

103
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,200
Let’s share this with your brother.

104
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:24,200
Pete, just eat your breakfast already
so we can leave.

105
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:28,760
I made your favorite minced pork, Ploy.

106
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:31,320
You could have given me more, Mom.

107
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:33,000
You can always ask for seconds, dear.

108
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:33,960
You’re the best.

109
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,200
Eat well, Pete.

110
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,280
I have something to tell you.

111
00:09:37,400 --> 00:09:39,640
Our hotel is right on the beach.

112
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:41,160
Your feet will touch the ocean
the moment you open the door.

113
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:41,760
Really?

114
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:42,440
You wanna go for a swim
with your old man?

115
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:43,240
Of course.

116
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,080
Alright, Pete?

117
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:45,160
Don’t hold back, son.

118
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:47,240
Is that what you’re wearing
to the beach, Pete?

119
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:49,840
What type of room is it again?

120
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:51,440
VIP, of course.

121
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:53,960
Don’t you know who your old man is?

122
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,840
How luxurious!

123
00:10:10,400 --> 00:10:17,000
PETE JIRAPAT PRUETICHAIANAN
WON FIRST GOLD IN 10 YEARS
FOR YUDO AT SEA GAMES

124
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:23,560
FIRST TROPHY FOR
HIGH SCHOOL YUDO

125
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:30,920
PETE JIRAPAT PRUETICHAIANAN
WON THAILAND’S 5TH
YOUTH YUDO CHAMPIONSHIP

126
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:02,040
Pete, are you ready, dear?

127
00:11:05,920 --> 00:11:06,480
Come on.

128
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:08,120
Your dad and Ploy are waiting.

129
00:11:08,280 --> 00:11:11,400
I want to be there to check in early
in case we can choose our room.

130
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,600
I’m sorry, Mom.

131
00:11:19,560 --> 00:11:21,480
I really can’t come with you.

132
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:22,440
Hey.

133
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:24,480
What’s going on?

134
00:11:25,680 --> 00:11:26,520
It’s your son.

135
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:28,200
He said he’s not coming with us.

136
00:11:28,680 --> 00:11:29,400
Why not, son?

137
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:34,200
It’s been a while since our family gets
to spend time together like this.

138
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:46,440
You’re right.

139
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:52,960
It’s been a while since I last
spent time with you both.

140
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,960
I just hope…

141
00:11:58,200 --> 00:12:00,040
I meet you again one day.

142
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:04,520
I hope we can live together,

143
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,080
spend time together.

144
00:12:11,920 --> 00:12:13,280
take a trip together,

145
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,040
be happy together.

146
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:24,240
But now isn’t the right time.

147
00:12:27,840 --> 00:12:30,600
I have something more important to do.

148
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,960
Please don’t be mad at me, you guys.

149
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:41,280
I’m sorry.

150
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:49,840
It’s okay, dear.

151
00:12:52,200 --> 00:12:56,320
How could we be mad at you
for continuing to live your life?

152
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:11,000
My champion.

153
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:53,000
Where are you, Niran?

154
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,040
Niran?

155
00:14:47,640 --> 00:14:48,640
Do I know you?

156
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:51,640
Hey.

157
00:14:52,240 --> 00:14:53,000
Niran, wait.

158
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:54,160
Hear me out.

159
00:14:54,440 --> 00:14:56,240
You’re not in the real world right now.

160
00:14:56,240 --> 00:14:57,440
You’re in the Life Spirit Realm.

161
00:14:57,720 --> 00:14:58,520
What realm?

162
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:02,480
Whatever the hell it is,
you need to come with me.

163
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:04,240
Come with you?

164
00:15:04,520 --> 00:15:05,200
No way.

165
00:15:05,760 --> 00:15:06,400
Why not?

166
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:12,960
Gung said I would never become Wu.

167
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:16,200
Hey.

168
00:15:16,680 --> 00:15:17,560
Where are you going?

169
00:15:17,880 --> 00:15:18,880
Suming School.

170
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:20,720
I’m going to train to become Wu.

171
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:29,880
Niran.

172
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:30,480
Come on.

173
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:32,440
Come back with me.

174
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:34,120
I said no.

175
00:15:34,320 --> 00:15:37,400
You seriously running away just ’cause
your grandpa said one mean thing?

176
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:38,480
Are you insane?

177
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:41,640
You keep walking but do you even
know where Suming School is?

178
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:47,920
Probably up there.

179
00:15:59,320 --> 00:15:59,800
Niran.

180
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:04,040
Don’t you feel that
nothing makes sense here?

181
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:08,040
You’re walking towards
you don’t even know where.

182
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:10,480
You know why?

183
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:13,360
Because this isn’t the real world.

184
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,560
Listen to me, Niran.

185
00:16:28,760 --> 00:16:32,360
One day in the future, you will become Wu.

186
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:35,120
You just need to come back with me.

187
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:41,040
When you open your eyes, you will realize
that you already are Wu.

188
00:16:42,640 --> 00:16:44,120
You don’t need to go anywhere.

189
00:16:44,560 --> 00:16:45,600
Believe me.

190
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:52,600
Hurts, doesn’t it?

191
00:16:52,800 --> 00:16:53,840
It’s not a dream.

192
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:55,280
Oh, you jerk.

193
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:56,440
So the getting on people’s nerves
starts young, huh?

194
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:58,640
Niran, wait!

195
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,120
Hey, Niran.

196
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:01,960
Wait up.

197
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:04,160
Niran, stop it.

198
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:05,079
Niran.

199
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:07,720
Hey!

200
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:11,839
Talk to me.

201
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:15,040
Niran, do you hear me?

202
00:17:16,520 --> 00:17:17,599
Ow, shit.

203
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:23,160
Hey.

204
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:24,079
Niran.

205
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:40,160
Niran.

206
00:17:41,560 --> 00:17:42,120
Niran.

207
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:49,240
Oh, idiot, look around you.

208
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:51,680
Niran, do you hear me?

209
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:57,560
Hey.

210
00:17:59,120 --> 00:17:59,600
Wait.

211
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,000
Shit.

212
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:05,600
Hey!

213
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,000
Niran!

214
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,640
You’ve been wasting two hours.

215
00:18:12,080 --> 00:18:12,880
You’ve had enough now?

216
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,240
You will never reach it.

217
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:16,840
I will reach it if I keep walking.

218
00:18:17,080 --> 00:18:19,440
Yeah? Does that mountain seem
any closer to you, though?

219
00:18:19,840 --> 00:18:21,000
It must.

220
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:22,360
I’ve been walking all this time.

221
00:18:22,520 --> 00:18:23,000
No.

222
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:24,680
It’s not closer.

223
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:27,560
And I can guarantee
you will never reach it.

224
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:33,760
Stop talking nonsense.

225
00:18:34,040 --> 00:18:36,120
I have to get to Suming today.

226
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,600
And I will become Wu.

227
00:18:37,640 --> 00:18:38,240
Really?

228
00:18:38,360 --> 00:18:40,480
How many times do you think
you’ve walked by this spot?

229
00:18:48,320 --> 00:18:50,200
Nothing is waiting for you
at the end of the road.

230
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:54,640
Because this isn’t the path of your real life.

231
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:57,520
You’re lost in the Life Spirit Realm.

232
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:02,600
If I don’t make it to Suming School,

233
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:05,520
that means…

234
00:19:07,920 --> 00:19:08,960
I’ll never become Wu.

235
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:20,520
You wanted to be Wu so badly?

236
00:19:22,840 --> 00:19:23,520
What about it?

237
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:25,920
Nothing.

238
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:40,880
Then how come you don’t believe me

239
00:19:43,200 --> 00:19:45,200
when I told you you’re already Wu?

240
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:53,280
Why are you running away from home
and walking to Suming School?

241
00:19:56,080 --> 00:19:58,600
You got through this part of your life
for a long time now.

242
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:30,760
You know what?

243
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:34,880
I was offended by my coach
as well when I was a kid.

244
00:20:38,840 --> 00:20:41,640
He said the likes of me
would never be an athlete.

245
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:42,840
But I didn’t care.

246
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:48,880
I just kept showing up to practice
again and again,

247
00:20:49,720 --> 00:20:50,720
and I got into a tournament.

248
00:20:54,560 --> 00:20:56,000
I won gold.

249
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:03,920
But in the end, I behaved so badly that
I got expelled from the association.

250
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:06,240
I didn’t even get a chance to turn pro.

251
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:09,560
So your coach was right?

252
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:13,920
You can say that.

253
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:19,560
But think carefully why I didn’t
become an athlete.

254
00:21:21,080 --> 00:21:24,560
Was it because of what my coach said
or my own action?

255
00:21:32,080 --> 00:21:32,640
Niran.

256
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:37,840
I don’t know why your grandpa said
what he said.

257
00:21:39,480 --> 00:21:41,000
But what does it matter?

258
00:21:42,880 --> 00:21:46,200
It’s what you choose to do and
the path you choose to walk on

259
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,480
that make you Wu.

260
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:57,920
Come back with me.

261
00:22:00,680 --> 00:22:02,840
Come back to your real life.

262
00:22:11,280 --> 00:22:12,960
Can I trust you, Pete?

263
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:21,400
Of course!

264
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:25,000
I swear you can totally freaking trust me.

265
00:22:30,520 --> 00:22:31,520
Come back with me.

266
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:43,240
Wu Yong Le!

267
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:46,160
Gung!

268
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:48,960
Gung!

269
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:50,560
Hey, Niran!

270
00:22:58,400 --> 00:22:59,120
Ow, fuc—

271
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:00,440
Oi!

272
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:02,080
What the hell are you standing there for?

273
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:03,400
You’re in the way!

274
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:09,360
Do I know you?

275
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:10,920
It’s me, Pete.

276
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:11,920
Pete who?

277
00:23:12,440 --> 00:23:13,160
I don’t know you.

278
00:23:13,880 --> 00:23:14,360
I’m in a hurry.

279
00:23:14,440 --> 00:23:15,120
Move away!

280
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:18,840
I’m here to get you back—Crap!

281
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:22,040
You jerk!

282
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,480
Can’t you get lost in the time
after we’ve met?

283
00:23:25,760 --> 00:23:27,560
This could have been easier, you idiot!

284
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:44,480
(You have to leave within eight hours,)

285
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:49,400
otherwise, you will be stuck there
and, eventually, devoured by it.

286
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:50,120
‘It’?

287
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:52,200
What do you mean?

288
00:23:52,640 --> 00:23:53,600
Taixu.

289
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:56,880
Also known as ‘the Eternal Void.’

290
00:23:57,000 --> 00:24:02,600
Its job is to clean up life spirits that have been in the Life Spirit Realm for too long

291
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:05,600
to maintain balance in the universe.

292
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,760
If you don’t bring Niran back in time,

293
00:24:09,120 --> 00:24:12,520
his life spirit will be wiped away
by Taixu as well.

294
00:24:12,720 --> 00:24:15,720
That means his being
will disappear for eternity.

295
00:24:41,520 --> 00:24:42,720
You’re impossible to defeat, huh?

296
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:47,720
You’ve evaded me 13 times.

297
00:24:49,320 --> 00:24:52,000
But this time, I’ll definitely get you.

298
00:24:53,080 --> 00:24:54,960
So this is the yao that caused
a blackout all through the city?

299
00:24:57,200 --> 00:24:59,360
This must be another thing
you can’t get over.

300
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:01,800
That’s why you want to
come back and defeat it.

301
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:02,920
Who the hell are you?

302
00:25:03,320 --> 00:25:04,160
What are you babbling?

303
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:06,120
I told you I don’t know you.

304
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,560
You don’t know me now.

305
00:25:09,440 --> 00:25:11,120
But you will give me this necklace later.

306
00:25:14,360 --> 00:25:15,680
Come back with me.

307
00:25:16,080 --> 00:25:17,480
You’re just wasting your time here.

308
00:25:22,720 --> 00:25:24,000
I can’t go anywhere with you.

309
00:25:25,240 --> 00:25:26,760
I have a duty to fulfill here.

310
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:31,320
This is the first task I received
from the elders Wu.

311
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:32,800
If I don’t succeed,

312
00:25:33,880 --> 00:25:35,720
they will never accept me my whole life.

313
00:25:35,840 --> 00:25:36,520
So what?

314
00:25:37,080 --> 00:25:37,920
What do you even care?

315
00:25:37,920 --> 00:25:38,840
Of course I do.

316
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:41,920
I won’t let myself become an outcast.

317
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:57,120
Alright.

318
00:25:57,560 --> 00:25:58,440
You jerk of a yao.

319
00:25:59,000 --> 00:25:59,720
Come at me!

320
00:26:05,600 --> 00:26:07,120
Stop it!

321
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:08,440
Stop trying to defeat it!

322
00:26:09,120 --> 00:26:10,160
You can’t win!

323
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:12,200
Because you never defeated it in real life!

324
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:14,360
What already happened
already happened!

325
00:26:14,360 --> 00:26:16,320
Why do you waste your time
thinking about it?

326
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:18,480
Just come back with me, you idiot!

327
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:50,880
You’re back.

328
00:27:05,800 --> 00:27:08,080
You are an obstinate one.

329
00:27:12,080 --> 00:27:16,200
A man whose compass in life

330
00:27:18,600 --> 00:27:20,960
is his obstinance
will be lost forever.

331
00:28:07,120 --> 00:28:08,560
What are you standing there for?

332
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:10,800
There’s plenty of seats for you to sit down.

333
00:28:14,800 --> 00:28:15,440
Niran.

334
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:17,640
I don’t care if you don’t know me right now.

335
00:28:17,720 --> 00:28:19,600
But you need to come back with me.

336
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:21,360
What are you saying, Pete?

337
00:28:22,520 --> 00:28:23,680
Why wouldn’t I know you?

338
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:28,560
So you know why I’m here?

339
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:31,280
You’re here to get me back
to defeat Qi Rong.

340
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:33,240
Yes.

341
00:28:34,280 --> 00:28:36,000
You need to come back and finish it.

342
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:38,080
There are so many people waiting for you.

343
00:28:44,320 --> 00:28:45,400
Even if I don’t,

344
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:49,040
someone will defeat it.

345
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:52,720
Jia Hao.

346
00:28:53,480 --> 00:28:54,400
Fei.

347
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:57,080
Or someone from the school.

348
00:28:58,920 --> 00:29:02,040
You know, maybe I’m not that important.

349
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:16,120
Where are you going, then?

350
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:19,640
Dunno.

351
00:29:20,840 --> 00:29:23,560
I’ll go wherever it takes me.

352
00:29:25,160 --> 00:29:26,480
It’s not taking you anywhere

353
00:29:26,760 --> 00:29:27,920
if you keep sitting here.

354
00:29:29,880 --> 00:29:30,720
Look.

355
00:29:31,800 --> 00:29:33,920
It’s devoured the entire atmosphere now.

356
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:35,320
You’re the only thing left.

357
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:38,920
No.

358
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:41,760
Everything looks normal to me.

359
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:43,920
Normal, my ass.

360
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:46,280
Don’t you see how empty it is outside?

361
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:47,720
You think that’s normal?

362
00:29:50,800 --> 00:29:53,800
Is your normal different from this?

363
00:29:55,360 --> 00:29:57,920
Wherever we are, whatever we do,

364
00:29:59,040 --> 00:30:00,120
or whatever we surround ourselves with,

365
00:30:02,080 --> 00:30:04,200
you think it matters?

366
00:30:05,440 --> 00:30:06,720
You jerk, but—

367
00:30:06,720 --> 00:30:07,200
Pete.

368
00:30:11,280 --> 00:30:12,840
Can’t I just sit down for once?

369
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:43,160
Sure thing.

370
00:30:45,480 --> 00:30:46,480
All I ask is that

371
00:30:49,400 --> 00:30:51,520
if things get risky around here,

372
00:30:53,280 --> 00:30:55,360
you need to let me get you out of here.

373
00:31:22,480 --> 00:31:23,440
You know,

374
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:26,640
I always dreamed of
when I was a kid.

375
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:31,080
I was running after a butterfly.

376
00:31:33,080 --> 00:31:35,120
Did you ever catch that butterfly
in your dream?

377
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:37,960
No.

378
00:31:41,200 --> 00:31:42,800
I was the butterfly in that dream,

379
00:31:44,480 --> 00:31:45,680
flying away from myself.

380
00:32:03,920 --> 00:32:04,360
Niran.

381
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:05,360
Where are you going?

382
00:32:06,320 --> 00:32:07,080
Niran.

383
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:08,240
Niran.

384
00:32:08,400 --> 00:32:09,040
Niran.

385
00:32:09,040 --> 00:32:10,040
Don’t go!

386
00:32:11,520 --> 00:32:12,120
Shit!

387
00:32:22,600 --> 00:32:23,600
(You are no Wu.)

388
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:26,000
(And you never will be.)

389
00:32:28,120 --> 00:32:29,640
(You are no Wu.)

390
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:31,800
(You are no Wu.)

391
00:32:31,800 --> 00:32:32,520
(You are no Wu.)

392
00:32:32,800 --> 00:32:33,880
(You are no Wu.)

393
00:32:33,880 --> 00:32:34,640
(You are no Wu.)

394
00:32:34,640 --> 00:32:35,200
(You are no Wu.)

395
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:36,160
(You are no Wu.)

396
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:56,360
Niran?

397
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,320
Niran!

398
00:33:18,680 --> 00:33:19,400
Niran.

399
00:33:22,560 --> 00:33:23,240
Niran!

400
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:24,240
Niran!

401
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:27,680
Niran!

402
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:28,880
Niran.

403
00:33:29,160 --> 00:33:30,120
Niran!

404
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:38,040
You’re still here?

405
00:33:47,240 --> 00:33:47,800
Niran.

406
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:51,080
Come back with me right now

407
00:33:51,960 --> 00:33:53,040
before you’re…

408
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:55,920
Shit.

409
00:34:00,840 --> 00:34:01,920
Shit. Shit.

410
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:03,880
Shit!

411
00:34:04,760 --> 00:34:05,200
Pete.

412
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:09,880
Thank you

413
00:34:11,159 --> 00:34:12,760
for coming all the way here to get me.

414
00:34:16,040 --> 00:34:17,520
But I think I like it here.

415
00:34:19,920 --> 00:34:21,560
What the hell are you talking about?

416
00:34:23,480 --> 00:34:24,800
I want to live here.

417
00:34:26,560 --> 00:34:27,440
You should go back.

418
00:34:28,199 --> 00:34:28,560
No.

419
00:34:29,639 --> 00:34:30,320
I’m not going back.

420
00:34:31,440 --> 00:34:32,880
Not unless you’re coming with me.

421
00:34:36,960 --> 00:34:37,639
Why?

422
00:34:40,520 --> 00:34:41,400
Why?

423
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:46,199
The life you’ve lived and
everything that you’ve done,

424
00:34:47,239 --> 00:34:50,120
you’re just going to let it
be devoured by this void?

425
00:34:58,760 --> 00:35:01,440
Do you think there is more to life than this?

426
00:35:03,320 --> 00:35:07,680
At least this void makes me feel nice.

427
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:09,880
Maybe…

428
00:35:12,520 --> 00:35:15,320
it will even bring me closer to heaven.

429
00:35:15,600 --> 00:35:16,080
No.

430
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:19,600
Not here.

431
00:35:20,120 --> 00:35:21,120
Don’t you get it?

432
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,880
Don’t you understand it can’t be here?

433
00:35:25,440 --> 00:35:27,040
You need to come back with me right now.

434
00:35:30,040 --> 00:35:32,120
I don’t care if you come back
and do nothing

435
00:35:32,120 --> 00:35:33,480
if you don’t want to.

436
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:38,120
You don’t want to defeat Qi Rong?

437
00:35:38,520 --> 00:35:39,160
Fine.

438
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:40,800
Let’s not do that.

439
00:35:42,120 --> 00:35:43,680
You don’t want to be Wu anymore?

440
00:35:44,520 --> 00:35:45,480
Okay!

441
00:35:46,480 --> 00:35:47,920
You don’t have to.

442
00:35:48,600 --> 00:35:52,440
I don’t know where the last place
that made you happy was.

443
00:35:53,960 --> 00:35:56,600
But it can’t be here, don’t you get it?

444
00:35:58,200 --> 00:36:00,120
You need to come back with me!

445
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:07,200
I can’t leave you here.

446
00:36:29,720 --> 00:36:30,960
Please.

447
00:36:35,600 --> 00:36:36,640
I’m begging you.

448
00:36:38,920 --> 00:36:40,160
Don’t do this.

449
00:36:42,240 --> 00:36:44,240
You’re not alone, you know!

450
00:36:44,800 --> 00:36:47,400
There are so many people waiting for you.

451
00:36:53,800 --> 00:36:58,360
You’re important to people,
at least to me.

452
00:37:00,480 --> 00:37:02,480
You’re very important to me.

453
00:37:10,520 --> 00:37:12,320
I can’t let you go like this.

454
00:37:13,600 --> 00:37:15,560
I can’t let you go.

455
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:20,280
Thank you, Pete.

456
00:37:23,240 --> 00:37:24,400
Thank you.

457
00:37:28,080 --> 00:37:29,760
But I think it’s too late.

458
00:37:30,120 --> 00:37:30,840
No.

459
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:35,600
No!

460
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:40,560
I don’t want to leave you here.

461
00:37:42,800 --> 00:37:43,960
Please.

462
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:49,720
You mean so much to everyone,

463
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:52,400
especially to me.

464
00:37:53,760 --> 00:37:55,160
Don’t you understand?

465
00:39:31,200 --> 00:39:32,120
Niran.

466
00:39:33,920 --> 00:39:35,080
If I go with you,

467
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:39,760
I’ll become Wu, won’t I?

468
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:51,640
Yes.

469
00:39:53,960 --> 00:39:55,880
You’ll be the coolest Wu ever.

470
00:39:59,200 --> 00:40:00,280
You know why?

471
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:04,400
Because you’ll have me as your partner.

472
00:40:09,080 --> 00:40:10,160
Will you come back with me?

473
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:45,720
JIA HAO

474
00:40:57,920 --> 00:40:58,800
Hello.

475
00:40:58,800 --> 00:40:59,960
How is Niran doing?

476
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:01,440
(Niran is awake now.)

477
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:56,440
What do we do now?

478
00:42:15,160 --> 00:42:15,840
Here.

479
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:17,920
These belonged to Mom.

480
00:42:18,640 --> 00:42:20,720
Uncle left them with me a long time ago.

481
00:42:21,040 --> 00:42:22,320
This part is yours.

482
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:26,280
I kept them because I didn’t want you
to gamble them all away.

483
00:42:27,720 --> 00:42:29,080
Since you quit now,

484
00:42:29,560 --> 00:42:31,320
I guess you can look after them yourself.

485
00:42:44,160 --> 00:42:46,120
Will you swear you won’t pawn them off?

486
00:42:47,120 --> 00:42:48,680
Yeah, I swear.

487
00:42:50,720 --> 00:42:52,960
I remember Mom wearing this all the time.

488
00:42:59,320 --> 00:43:01,600
You only asked me to swear
not to pawn them off, right?

489
00:43:10,960 --> 00:43:11,440
Here.

490
00:43:14,960 --> 00:43:16,280
For leaving the hospital.

491
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:16,800
Huh?

492
00:43:19,800 --> 00:43:20,880
It belonged to my Mom.

493
00:43:21,840 --> 00:43:24,880
I just learned she left me something
before she died.

494
00:43:25,640 --> 00:43:27,440
You gave me something of your grandpa’s.

495
00:43:28,640 --> 00:43:30,440
I want to give you something of
my Mom’s in return.

496
00:43:36,360 --> 00:43:40,360
I don’t know if it has power
like yours, though.

497
00:43:47,560 --> 00:43:48,120
It does.

498
00:43:49,360 --> 00:43:53,160
Every piece of jade that’s passed
from one hand to the next

499
00:43:54,080 --> 00:43:56,520
gathers the power to protect its owner.

500
00:44:02,440 --> 00:44:04,560
But are you sure you want to—

501
00:44:04,560 --> 00:44:05,000
Yep.

502
00:44:08,000 --> 00:44:08,840
It’s for you.

503
00:44:13,080 --> 00:44:14,280
And if it has power,

504
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:18,560
I want that power to protect you.

505
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:24,760
Okay.

506
00:44:31,080 --> 00:44:32,240
Hey, wait!

507
00:44:32,600 --> 00:44:34,040
Why did you have to put it on that finger?

508
00:44:34,840 --> 00:44:36,160
Why not?

509
00:44:36,880 --> 00:44:37,920
It fits.

510
00:44:50,600 --> 00:44:51,520
Forget it.

511
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:52,680
It’s no big deal.

512
00:44:52,760 --> 00:44:53,280
Yeah.

513
00:44:54,840 --> 00:44:55,640
Crap.

514
00:44:55,640 --> 00:44:57,800
Who cares about that?

515
00:44:59,920 --> 00:45:02,080
Li Puo is definitely planning something.

516
00:45:02,640 --> 00:45:06,480
The power of Lord Warrior
has blanketed this entire city.

517
00:45:09,840 --> 00:45:13,280
You know how to deal with Qi Rong now?

518
00:45:14,280 --> 00:45:16,320
I’ll let heaven and earth decide.

519
00:45:17,000 --> 00:45:20,600
Any power that defies heaven
does not last long.

520
00:45:20,800 --> 00:45:23,520
At least I have you
who truly believes in me.
